library(tidylab)
library(tidylog)
library(tidyverse)
library(ggplot2)
library(skimr)
library(readr)
omega = read_csv("OMEGA_2000.csv")
drg = read_csv("DRG.csv")
descriptor = read_csv("DISPOSTN.csv")
main_table =
  omega %>% 
  left_join(drg, by = "DRG")
head(main_table)
cardioORortho =
main_table %>% 
  filter((DRG > 102 & DRG < 146)|(DRG > 208 & DRG < 257))
head(cardioORortho)
question1 = 
  cardioORortho %>% 
  mutate(category = if_else(DRG > 102 & DRG < 146, 'Cardiac','Ortho'))

Question III.1

Profitability of patients from Cardiac and Orthopedic services

question1 %>% 
  group_by(category) %>% 
  summarize(sum_of_totalpayment = sum(TOT_PAY), sum_of_totalcost = sum(TOT_COST), na.rm = TRUE) %>% 
  mutate(profitability = (sum_of_totalpayment - sum_of_totalcost)/sum_of_totalpayment) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x =category, y = profitability, fill = category)) +
  geom_col(width = 0.6) +
  theme_bw() +
  labs(x = "Service Name", y = "Profitability", title = "Profitability of patients from Cardiac and Orthopedic services")

Question III.1.1

profitability for all services

Compare it to whole hospital and other service lines

question1.1 =
  left_join(x = omega, y = drg, by = "DRG")
question1.1 %>% 
  group_by(MAJ_DX_CAT) %>% 
  filter(MAJ_DX_CAT != "**") %>% 
  summarize(sum_of_totalpayment = sum(TOT_PAY), sum_of_totalcost = sum(TOT_COST), na.rm = TRUE) %>% 
  mutate(profitability = (sum_of_totalpayment - sum_of_totalcost)/sum_of_totalpayment) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = MAJ_DX_CAT, y = profitability, fill = MAJ_DX_CAT)) + 
  geom_col(width = 0.5) +
  labs(x = "diagnosis category",  y = "profitability", title = "varied diagnosis versus their profitability to the unit")

#creating categories for profit

omega = omega %>% 
   mutate(diff_services = case_when(
     (DRG > 0 & DRG < 36) ~ 'Neural',
     (DRG > 35 & DRG < 49) ~ 'Opth',
     (DRG > 48 & DRG < 75) ~ 'ENT',
     (DRG > 102 & DRG < 146) ~ 'Cardiac',
     (DRG > 208 & DRG < 257) ~ 'Ortho', TRUE~ 'Others'))
omega %>% 
  group_by(diff_services) %>% 
  summarize(sum_of_totalpayment = sum(TOT_PAY),
            sum_of_totalcost = sum(TOT_COST)) %>% 
  mutate(profitability = (sum_of_totalpayment - sum_of_totalcost)/sum_of_totalpayment) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = reorder(diff_services, - profitability), y = profitability, fill = diff_services)) +
  geom_col() +
   labs(x = "major services",  y = "profitability", title = "Services versus their profitability to the unit")

#Visuals of major services and their LOS: indication of outliars

omega %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = diff_services, y = LOS))+
  geom_boxplot(aes(diff_services, LOS, color = diff_services)) + 
  theme_bw() +
  coord_cartesian(ylim = c(1,40)) +
  labs(x= "Varied Services", y= "Length of Stay", title="Length of stay versus Services in the hospital")

Cardio and Ortho

question1 %>% 
  group_by(category) %>% 
  summarize(average_LOS = mean(LOS))

Visual

ggplot(data = question1, mapping = aes(x = LOS)) +
geom_histogram(binwidth = 2, color = "yellow") +
facet_wrap(~category) +
geom_vline(aes(xintercept = mean(LOS)), color = 'blue') +
theme_bw() +
  labs(title = "Length of Stay for cardiac and Ortho", x = "Length of Stay", y = "Number of patients")

#Outliars

ggplot(data = question1, mapping = aes(x = category, y = LOS)) +
geom_boxplot(mapping = aes(category, LOS, color = category), position = "dodge") +
theme_bw() +
coord_cartesian(ylim = c(1,40))

labs(title = "Length of Stay for cardiac and Ortho", x = "Length of Stay", y = "Number of patients")

Question III.3

Payer mix

question3 = 
  omega %>%
  group_by(PRIM_PAY, SEC_PAY, MAJOR_PAY) %>% 
  summarize(number_of_payer_type = n()) %>% 
  mutate(prop = number_of_payer_type/sum(number_of_payer_type)) %>% 
  arrange(desc(number_of_payer_type))
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'PRIM_PAY', 'SEC_PAY'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
question3visual = 
  question3 %>% 
  group_by(PRIM_PAY) %>% 
  summarize(payer_mix = n()) %>% 
  mutate(payer_mix = payer_mix) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = reorder(PRIM_PAY, -payer_mix), y = payer_mix, fill = payer_mix)) +
  geom_bar(stat = 'identity') +
  labs(title = "Number of patient for different payer mix", x = "payer type", y = "number of patients") +
  theme_bw()

question3visual

question3visual = 
  question3 %>% 
  group_by(SEC_PAY) %>% 
  summarize(payer_mix = n()) %>% 
  mutate(payer_mix = payer_mix) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = reorder(SEC_PAY, -payer_mix), y = payer_mix, fill = payer_mix)) +
  geom_bar(stat = 'identity') +
  labs(title = "Number of patient for different payer mix", x = "payer type", y = "number of patients") +
  theme_bw()

question3visual

Question III.4

finding the right table

question4 =
  left_join(x = question1.1, y = descriptor, by = "DISPOSTN")

ATable for all services

question4.1 =
  question4 %>% 
  filter(ADM_TYPE == 'EMERGENT' | ADM_TYPE == 'ELECTIVE', na.rm = TRUE) %>% 
  group_by(ADM_TYPE, DESCRIPT) %>% 
  summarize(number_of_records = n()) %>% 
  mutate(prop = number_of_records/sum(number_of_records)) %>% 
  arrange(desc(number_of_records))
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'ADM_TYPE'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
question4.1

For cardiac and Ortho

question4.2 = 
  subset(question4, select=c(MAJ_DX_CAT,ADM_TYPE,DESCRIPT), 
  subset = MAJ_DX_CAT == "08" | MAJ_DX_CAT == "05")
question4.21 = 
  question4.2 %>% 
  group_by(MAJ_DX_CAT,ADM_TYPE) %>% 
  summarize(number_of_records = n()) %>% 
  mutate(number_of_records = number_of_records) 
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'MAJ_DX_CAT'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
  
question4.21 =  
  filter(question4.21, ADM_TYPE == 'EMERGENT'| ADM_TYPE == 'ELECTIVE')

question4.21 %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = MAJ_DX_CAT, y = number_of_records, fill= ADM_TYPE))+
  geom_bar(stat = 'identity', position = 'dodge')+
  labs(x= "Admission Type", y= "Number Of Patients", title="Rates of emergent versus elective care for cardiology (05) and Orthopedics (08)") + 
  theme_bw()
